claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table listing licensed seasonal influenza vaccines for the 2022–23 season, including vaccine names/manufacturers, presentations (e.g., 0.5-mL prefilled syringe), age indications, hemagglutinin content per dose (µg/0.5 mL), route of administration, and footnotes. Flublok Quadrivalent (recombinant HA vaccine) is listed with 45 µg HA per 0.5 mL dose for ages ≥18 years given intramuscularly. The table provides formulation and dosing details for Flublok but contains no information on antigenic matching to WHO- or FDA-selected flu strains, so it does not support the claim.
